
# 🔐 LogSentinel – Log Analysis & Threat Detection System

A Flask-based web application that analyzes server log files to detect suspicious activity, classify risk levels, and generate security reports.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 📂 Upload log files (.log / .txt)
- 🔍 Analyze user/IP activity
- ⚠️ Detect suspicious behavior
- 📊 Risk scoring system:
  - 🟢 Safe (1–5 requests)
  - 🟡 Low Risk (6–10)
  - 🟠 Medium Risk (11–15)
  - 🔴 High Risk (16+)
- 📄 Generate downloadable PDF reports
- 📈 Dashboard with insights
- 🔐 Session-based user privacy (no data leakage)

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Python
- Flask
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- ReportLab
- HTML, CSS


## How to Run
1. Install Flask: pip install flask
2. Run: python app.py
3. Open: http://127.0.0.1:5000/

## Use Case
This project helps identify potential cybersecurity threats from server logs and can be extended for SIEM-like systems.

## Project Highlights
Implemented real-world log analysis logic
Designed a risk classification system
Ensured user data isolation using Flask sessions
Deployed on cloud using Render

